        EV Score (Expected Value Score) rates your rack quality from 0 to 100. It evaluates five factors:
        <strong class="text-gray-300">vowel balance</strong> (ideal 2-3 vowels),
        <strong class="text-gray-300">power tiles</strong> (S, blanks, J/Q/X/Z),
        <strong class="text-gray-300">bingo potential</strong> (overlap with known bingo stems like SATIRE, RETINA),
        <strong class="text-gray-300">letter synergy</strong> (common affixes like -ING, -TION, -ED), and
        <strong class="text-gray-300">duplicate penalty</strong> (repeated letters reduce flexibility).
        A higher score means your rack has better word-building potential. Scores above 65 are Strong, above 80 Excellent.
